wo samples used in the original study. This study shows that, for LA (Low\nAlpha between 2 and 50 alpha/khr-cm$^2$) sample measurements, the only\nremaining site-to-site variations were due to counting statistics. Variations\nin ULA (Ultra-Low Alpha < 2 alpha/khr-cm$^2$) sample measurements were reduced\nthree-fold, compared to the earlier study, with the measurements suggesting\nthat residual activity variations now primarily arise from site-to-site\ndifferences in the cosmogenic background.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Jan 2014 21:45:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 4 Mar 2014 00:24:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-04-17"}
